---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LabelRow from '../components/LabelRow.astro';
import CtaStrip from '../components/CtaStrip.astro';

const facts = [
  ['Based', 'Minneapolis, MN'],
  ['Available', 'Remote, US-wide'],
  ['Reply time', '\u2264 2 business days'],
  ['Past experience', 'Finance, academia, retail'],
  ['Tech stack', 'Whatever fits the job'],
  ['Meeting style', 'In person where possible']
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — NSG Solutions"
  description="Noah Greensweig runs NSG Solutions, a one-person custom software practice in Minneapolis. End-to-end engagements, no handoffs, no account managers."
  breadcrumb={[
    { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { name: 'About', href: '/about' }
  ]}
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="about-hero">
        <div>
          <LabelRow num="ABOUT / 01" meta="The person behind it" />
          <h1>I'm Noah.<br /><em>I run a small software practice<br />out of Minneapolis.</em></h1>
        </div>
        <div class="about-photo-frame">
          <img src="/assets/noah.jpg" alt="Noah Greensweig, founder of NSG Solutions" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <div class="about-photo-tag"><span class="dash"></span>Noah Greensweig &middot; Minneapolis, MN</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">02 / WHAT THIS IS</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            NSG is a small software practice. The whole thing is one person: I take on
            a handful of client engagements at a time, I do the work end-to-end, and the
            person you talk to is the same person writing the code.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most recently, I built automation systems and led AI adoption inside a reinsurance
            brokerage. NSG is where I bring that to businesses that want a real tool, not a
            slide deck about one.
          </p>
          <p>
            The pitch is plain. Most small businesses are still waiting on technology
            they should have had years ago. NSG&rsquo;s job is closing that gap. The website,
            the internal tools, the automations. And when those are solid, the AI that
            quietly takes over the parts that used to take a person. One practice,
            start to finish.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">03 / HOW IT WORKS</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            We meet, in person if you&rsquo;re in or near Minneapolis, video otherwise.
            You walk me through what&rsquo;s getting in the way of the work. I ask a lot of
            questions, take notes, and come back with a plain-language proposal. What
            the fix looks like, what it costs (hourly rate, or a fixed bid for well-defined work),
            and when you&rsquo;ll have it.
          </p>
          <p>
            Then we build, together. You see the work as it goes, not in a reveal at the end.
            Things change as we learn. That&rsquo;s fine. The point isn&rsquo;t to defend the original
            plan, it&rsquo;s to land the right thing.
          </p>
          <p>
            When it&rsquo;s done, it&rsquo;s yours. I write things so a person who isn&rsquo;t me can keep
            them running. If something we previously agreed was finished later turns out to
            be broken, fixing it is free.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 04 / ON AI — reframed around the progression story.
           AI sits at the top of a stack; only works when the foundation is right;
           NSG handles both. Said plainly. -->
      <section class="about-prose">
        <div class="label-col">04 / ON AI</div>
        <div class="body-col">
          <p>
            Most AI work doesn&rsquo;t fail because the AI is bad. It fails because it&rsquo;s
            plugged into a process that was never solid to begin with. The spreadsheet is still the
            source of truth. The website is half-broken. The data lives in three places.
          </p>

          <div class="about-stack-mini" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="row t3"><span class="num">03</span><span class="name">Intelligence</span><span class="bar"></span></div>
            <div class="row t2"><span class="num">02</span><span class="name">Operations</span><span class="bar"></span></div>
            <div class="row t1"><span class="num">01</span><span class="name">Foundation</span><span class="bar"></span></div>
          </div>

          <p>
            AI sits at the top of a stack. Below it, a working website, software shaped
            to the operation, tools that talk to each other. Skip those, and the AI
            step is sitting on quicksand.
          </p>
          <p>
            NSG does the whole stack. The website, the internal tool, the wiring between
            them, and then, when the foundation&rsquo;s right, the AI integration that
            quietly takes over the parts a person used to do. <em>One person. No handoffs.</em>
          </p>
          <p>
            The other honest thing about AI right now: the landscape moves every few months.
            Part of my job is keeping track so you don&rsquo;t have to, and picking the tool
            that fits your situation, not the thing that&rsquo;s trending this week. Used carefully,
            it makes the work faster and cheaper without dropping the quality. Used carelessly,
            it makes a confident mess. Most of the craft now is knowing the difference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="about-facts">
        <LabelRow num="05 / AT A GLANCE" meta="The short version" />
        <div class="facts-grid">
          {facts.map(([key, value]) => (
            <div class="fact">
              <div class="key">{key}</div>
              <div class="val" set:html={value}></div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <CtaStrip
      title="Want to talk?"
      continuation="Tell me what's going on."
      note="Two business-day reply &middot; No commitment until you&rsquo;re ready"
      primaryText="Get in touch"
      ghostText="Email directly"
    />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
